Again, Netflix=E2=80=99s 65 million number is global, so this once again is=
n=E2=80=99t an apples-to-apples comparison, but there is definitely a good =
chance this event would make the top ten.

Customer Acquisition vs. Churn Mitigation
-----------------------------------------

You noticed, I=E2=80=99m sure, the extent to which football, particularly t=
he NFL, dominated that list of most seen events. To that end, Netflix didn=
=E2=80=99t =E2=80=94 contra that Bloomberg excerpt =E2=80=94 have any ads i=
n the brodcast (although there were ringside sponsors); they did, however, =
run promos for their upcoming Christmas-slate of NFL games between rounds. =
And, on Monday, they added one more piece of news; from Bloomberg ( https:/=
/www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-18/beyonce-to-join-netflix-s-nfl-d=
ebut-in-coup-for-mega-events-push ) :

Beyonc=C3=A9 will headline the halftime show during Netflix Inc.=E2=80=99s =
maiden foray into live NFL games this Christmas, a big score for a US compa=
ny betting big on live sports and mega-events. Netflix, which in May secure=
d the rights to air two National Football League games this Christmas, drop=
ped the surprise announcement after streaming one of the most-watched boxin=
g matchups of all time. The Grammy-winning artist will perform songs from h=
er latest Cowboy Carter album for the first time during a contest between t=
he Houston Texans and Baltimore Ravens in her hometown. She=E2=80=99s expec=
ted to invite =E2=80=9Cspecial guests,=E2=80=9D Netflix said without elabor=
ating.

Beyonc=C3=A9 has appeared at NFL football games previously: she headlined t=
he 2013 Super Bowl and appeared as a guest at the 2016 Super Bowl. Those ar=
e, as you can tell from the above numbers, the biggest events of all, and s=
peak, I suspect, to Netflix=E2=80=99s ambitions for this broadcast: Netflix=
 isn=E2=80=99t treating Christmas Day as a couple of regular season games, =
but rather as events. That=E2=80=99s exactly what co-CEO Ted Sarandos promi=
sed on the company=E2=80=99s second quarter earnings call ( https://s22.q4c=
dn.com/959853165/files/doc_events/2024/Jul/18/netflix-inc-usa-d815629a-440e=
-4f6b-9f5e-831213418dd0.pdf ) :

*How do you thread the needle on licensing sports to drive advertising spen=
d without becoming beholden to leagues at renewal?*

Well, hopefully, exactly the way we=E2=80=99re doing it, by making these Ne=
tflix events, not necessarily taking on a lot of tonnage from any one leagu=
e, by actually making these games events like having two NFL football games=
 on Christmas Day and two great games, the Chiefs and the Steelers and the =
Ravens and the Texans. They=E2=80=99re both going to be great games, and it=
 really creates a lot of real excitement with the service, and it=E2=80=99s=
 one day of football.

This lined up with how I characterized Netflix=E2=80=99s strategy when they=
 signed the deal in May ( https://stratechery.com/2024/netflix-and-the-nfl-=
netflix-internalizes-ads-comcasts-bundle/?access_token=3DeyJhbGciOiJSUzI1Ni=
